# T-number

T-number is a number $ N $ of that satisfies the following conditions.

"A natural number $ N $ is an n-digit number that can be expressed as the product of two different prime numbers $ p, q $. The natural number $ M $, which is obtained by reversing the order of the digits of $ N $, is also a natural number that can be expressed as the product of three different prime numbers $ r, s, t $. where p, q, r, s, and t are different"
